<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10069g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10069g">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10069g"> 69(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> monument Chappe / rue du Bac</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;est des hommes de g&eacute;nie comme <mark>Chappe</mark>, que parlait B&eacute;ranger dans ces vers: &hellip; En effet, on lui a &eacute;lev&eacute; sur le boulevard Saint-Germain, &agrave; l&apos;intersection de la <mark>rue du Bac</mark> et du boulevard Raspail, <mark>une statue en bronze</mark> &hellip;, gr&acirc;ce &agrave; M. Jacquez, biblioth&eacute;caire du minist&egrave;re des Postes et T&eacute;l&eacute;graphes, qui a pris l&apos;initiative de la souscription. <font color="green">[B&eacute;ranger spoke of men of genius like Chappe in these verses: [&hellip;]</font> Indeed, a bronze statue of him was raised on the Boulevard St Germain, at the intersection of the Rue du Bac and the Boulevard Raspail <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>, thanks to Mr Jacquez, librarian to the Ministery of Posts and Telegraphs, who took the initiative of raising funds.] <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 314</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
